Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, El Brocal, Ferreyros, IRL, Pacasmayo

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-02-18T18:14:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/peru-stocks-buenaventura-el-brocal-ferreyros-irl-pacasmayo.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:55 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose 0.7 percent to 22,942.71. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 1.2 percent to 3,114.82.  Miners rose after metals futures advanced in New York and
London, said Miguel Pajuelo, an analyst at Lima-based Juan Magot
y Asociados SAB.    Minera IRL Ltd . (MIRL PE), a U.K. minerals explorer with a
gold mine in Peru, jumped 6.3 percent to $1.35. Cia. de Minas
Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest precious-metals
miner, gained for the fourth session in five, adding 4.6 percent
to $45.10. Soc. Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and
lead producer, rose 2.8 percent to 58.50 soles.  Construction industry-related stocks gained after Finance
Minister Ismael Benavides said Peru’s economy will expand 7.5
percent this year.    Ferreyros SA  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., advanced 2.3 percent to 4.50 soles.  Cementos
Pacasmayo SAA  (CPACASC1 PE), the Hochschild Group’s cement
producer, rose 1.9 percent to 7.90 soles after announcing
fourth-quarter net income rose 10 percent to 48.7 million soles
($17.6 million).  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  